net.sourceforge.waters.model.compiler.context

Class OccursChecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sourceforge.waters.model.base.DefaultProxyVisitor
      • net.sourceforge.waters.model.module.DefaultModuleProxyVisitor
        • net.sourceforge.waters.model.compiler.context.OccursChecker
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProxyVisitor, ModuleProxyVisitor

    public class OccursChecker
extends DefaultModuleProxyVisitor
    A simple implementation of the occurs-check. The occurs-check is needed to determine whether a given expression contains a particular subterm. It is used by the EFA compiler to check whether expressions contain particular variables, e.g., to avoid cyclic bindings.
    Author:
    Robi Malik
